## Codex-specific

- Use skills for repeatable workflows instead of expanding this file with long
  runbooks. Skills live in `~/.agents/skills` (a symlink to `~/.claude/skills`,
  the single source shared with Claude/opencode/pi).
- Reach for `env-reconciler` early when entering an unfamiliar repository,
  reconciling toolchains, or mapping how to validate a project.
- For source-grounded research, prefer primary documentation and concrete local
  evidence.
- Use MCPs and web search for current external APIs, libraries, standards, and
  product docs; cite sources when research informs the answer.
- Keep repo-specific behavior in project `AGENTS.md` or `CLAUDE.md`, not in
  this global file.
